# Lecture

### **Team dynamics in new venture creation**

_“In this lecture, we will talk about how to foster team performance through teamwork. We will talk about how an average team can outperform a team of stars; why diversity is not necessarily good for performance; why working in a team can both be wonderful and very difficult. Most importantly, we will talk about how to enable better teamwork in YOUR teams.”._

![](data:image/png;base64,)

What best predicts collective intelligence in teams? →

The good news

- We cannot do much about our intelligence (even though most people believe they are smarter than the average)![](data:image/png;base64,)
- But that’s OK – what seems to matter more is how we collaborate, not how smart we are.

_A team can be better than its individual members!_

What matters for performance? →

| **1\. Forming** | _Relationships:_ people are pleasant and polite<br><br>_Task_: Focus on relationship more than the task<br><br>_Phase characteristics:_ Team members are comfortable and positive, but typically not very productive |
| --- | --- |
| **2\. Storming** | _Relationships:_ people start to clash as they become less polite and more “true” to themselves<br><br>_Task_: as the weight of the task hits, people might have different opinions about what to do and how to do it<br><br>_Phase characteristics:_ conflict, questioning of leadership |
| --- | --- |
| **3\. Norming** | _Relationships:_ People start coming together as a team<br><br>_Task_: Reach a common understanding about how to organize work in the team<br><br>_Phase characteristics:_ Develops from individuals who work together into a TEAM |
| --- | --- |
| **4\. Performing** | _Relationships:_ People know each other and how to work together. They are a unit.<br><br>_Task_: People know what to do and how to do it. They have a common goal to<br><br>reach for.<br><br>_Phase characteristics:_ This is when the work<br><br>gets done |
| --- | --- |
| **5\. Adjourning** | _Relationships:_ People feel a sense of loss that the team is no longer there<br><br>_Task_: Team members can feel proud (or disappointed) about what they accomplished, but also a little lost after having worked for some time towards a clear goal and deadline<br><br>_Phase characteristics:_ Members mourn that their experience is now over. |
| --- | --- |

Some useful tips moving forward

- Be clear about your goals – as a team and as individuals
- Communicate openly and honestly about how you feel
- Say what you think – your team members are not mind readers
- Conflicts will come – but try to avoid making them personal and address them as immediately as you can
